# Build-context hygiene — keep `docker build` fast and reproducible.
# The Dockerfile COPYs only: CMakeLists.txt, src, third_party, tests, nets,
# tools, trainer/nnue_samples.txt. Everything below is noise in the context
# (and some of it — host build dirs, local experiment nets — is large).

# Version control & editor cruft
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.claude

# Out-of-tree / accidental in-source build artifacts (never needed in the image;
# the image always configures a fresh `build/` via `cmake -B build`)
build/
build-nnue/
CMakeFiles/
CMakeCache.txt
Makefile
*.o
*.obj
*.exe

# Local-only experiment nets are gitignored; keep only the committed nets the
# build can actually embed (NNUE_NET default = nets/king_int8_174m.bin).
nets/*.bin
!nets/king_int8_174m.bin
!nets/king_ob8_174m.bin
!nets/king_nnue.bin

# Training data, datasets, numpy caches, logs, PGNs, the rules PDF, error logs.
# The engine image needs NOTHING from data/ or trainer/ (the NNUE net is embedded
# from nets/, the bit-exact sample gate is unit-tests-only and not built here).
data/
trainer/
*.pgn
*.log
*.err
*.npz
*.pdf

# Large Texel dataset & baseline binaries under tools/ (embed_net.py is kept)
tools/*.epd
tools/*.epd.gz
tools/baseline/

# Host-side harness files (the organizer supplies its own copies; the engine
# inside the image never needs them)
engine-adapter.sh
openings.bin
